```json
{
  "application": "ATHAM",
  "software": [
    "netcdf-fortran/4.6.1-gcc-12.3.0-6scz",
    "parallel-netcdf/1.12.3-gcc-12.3.0-hi72"
  ],
  "resources": {
    "nodes": 2,
    "cores_per_node": 32,
    "mpi_processes_per_node": 32,
    "walltime": "168:00:00"
  },
  "input_files": [
    "INPUT_atham_setup_small_grid_22_5m",
    "INPUT_profile_20mps_trop_step_8km",
    "INPUT_volcano_22_5_300",
    "INPUT_dynamic_setup"
  ],
  "output_directory": "/scratch/palatyle/tropical_step22_5m_300ms_20ms",
  "output_file_prefix": "atham"
}
```

This script runs the ATHAM application. It uses the following software:

* netcdf-fortran/4.6.1-gcc-12.3.0-6scz
* parallel-netcdf/1.12.3-gcc-12.3.0-hi72

It also requires the following resources:

* 2 nodes
* 32 cores per node
* 32 MPI processes per node
* A walltime of 168 hours

The script sets the input and output directories, as well as the input and output file names. The input files are:

* INPUT_atham_setup_small_grid_22_5m
* INPUT_profile_20mps_trop_step_8km
* INPUT_volcano_22_5_300
* INPUT_dynamic_setup

The output directory is:

* /scratch/palatyle/tropical_step22_5m_300ms_20ms

The output file prefix is:

* atham
